To analyze the maximum working capacity of OSCs, open-circuit voltage (Voc) plays a vital role. It is the determination of entire quantity of current that is generated by an optical material47. A higher value of Voc can be attained whereas the LUMO level of the acceptor has a higher energy value and the HOMO of the donor has a lower value48. By utilizing following Equation, Voc can be calculated46.1Voc=EHOMOD-ELUMOA-0.3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
