Binding energy (Eb) is also considered a vital factor for evaluating the photovoltaic properties of OSCs particularly exciton dissociation capacity49,50. Binding energy is a noticeable parameter for determining the columbic force interaction among hole and electrons. In the excited state, lower columbic interaction between electron and hole and greater the exciton dissociation51,52. Eopt is a term that refers to the energy of the S0–S151,52. Equation (2) is used to measure Eb.2Eb=EH-LEopt\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
